SPECIAL SEMINAR ON PSYCHOLOGY

52
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:59,000
I remember Jay Chou had a song

53
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,040
called "Her Eyelashes."

54
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,840
When I was in high school,

55
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:06,040
the song was often played
during the lunch break.

56
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:09,040
I liked memorizing vocabulary
at lunchtime,

57
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,120
while my deskmate

58
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,880
liked napping on the table.

59
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:16,680
Whenever I closed my textbook
to memorize the words,

60
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:20,280
I always saw her long eyelashes
in the corner of my eye.

61
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:23,480
But later on, I gave up
memorizing vocabulary at lunchtime

62
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:25,920
because it was so ineffective.

63
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,720
I wasn't sure if it was that song

64
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,960
that affected me

65
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:31,880
or something else.

66
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,360
That was until I learned a certain word.

67
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:40,640
"Fluttering."

68
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,920
I wonder if you have ever felt this way.

69
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,120
When someone becomes special to you,

70
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:50,160
you just can't seem
to keep your eyes off them.

71
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,320
That's so accurate.

72
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:55,720
Even a simple smile

73
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:59,160
or sudden eye contact

74
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,400
will be caught by someone who cares.

75
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,600
They will remain excited for a long time.

76
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,800
Some of you here

77
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:09,400
must've had similar experiences.

78
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:13,280
The feeling is both confusing

79
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,840
and novel.

80
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:17,079
In fact,

81
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,440
these are all normal parts of adolescence.

82
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,120
I don't think he was right at all.

83
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,320
"We become sneaky

84
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:29,960
when we like someone"?

85
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:31,800
I don't think so.

86
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:35,040
He said "careful," not "sneaky."

87
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,400
That's more or less the same.

88
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,760
Anyway, if I like someone,

89
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,880
I would show it openly

90
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:43,200
and let everyone know about it.

91
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,040
How about you, Lurang?

92
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:50,120
I think you would be the sneaky type.

93
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,160
Figure yourself out first.

94
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,040
How rare!

95
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,520
You're not buying snacks.

96
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,000
Jiangjiang spent a fortune yesterday

97
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,400
on a beautiful glass jar,

98
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,800
so she has used up all her money.

99
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:10,880
It's all right.

100
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:12,080
You can eat mine.

101
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,360
Why did you buy a glass jar?

102
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,120
It's a secret.

103
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,120
That's right.

104
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,160
I just got my contest prize money.

105
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,640
Take your pick. It's on me.

106
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,440
Thank you.

107
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,560
Don't grab too much.

108
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,760
You're a hearty eater.

109
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,160
Gu Ran, you're awesome.

110
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,840
I'll help myself then.

111
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,080
Rangrang, these are delicious. Take them.

112
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:50,080
Do you know what will appear on your face

113
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,440
after eating too much junk food?

114
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:55,080
A smile?

115
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,440
You're exceptionally handsome today.

116
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,280
You're handsome.

117
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,560
Shall we?

118
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:13,840
Let's go.

119
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,400
Doesn't he seem a bit too happy today?

120
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,440
Look at that girl.

121
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,240
She's quite pretty.

122
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:38,040
I also think her hair clip is pretty.

123
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,600
Jiang Jia has an identical one.

124
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:40,840
It's pink.

125
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,960
I think it looks cuter
on Jiang Jia though.

126
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,400
I mean,

127
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,480
Jiang Jia has a bigger face,

128
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,920
so it suits her better.

129
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:58,560
That's all.

130
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:00,560
Let's go.

131
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,680
It's a beautiful sunny day.

132
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,360
Do you know?

133
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:17,200
He had just bit it
and the teacher called him.

134
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,800
So he spat it all out into his hands.

135
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,000
Su Zaizai.

136
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,360
Where's Jiang Jia?

137
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,000
She went to see Qianyu.

138
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,920
She has something important to do.

139
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:35,400
I just remembered that
I forgot my homework. I'll go get it.

140
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,240
You guys go ahead. Don't wait for me.

141
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,080
{\an8}There should be no one around
at this hour, right?

142
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,400
Which one

143
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:11,120
is Qianyu's seat?

144
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,160
"Li Cheng."

145
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,240
"Huang Ming."

146
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,440
"Wang Zhi."

147
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,440
Found it.

148
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,000
What are you doing in our classroom?

149
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:40,840
I...

150
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:44,440
Sorry, I just came to drop something off.

151
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,160
Gu Ran,

152
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,320
how could you scare people
at night like that?

153
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:01,480
