266
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:13,680
I think it's pretty good.

267
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:16,720
I've never written a love letter though.

268
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,520
I'm not sure if this is how it is written.

269
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,040
You're so good at writing essays,

270
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,480
so you should be fine.

271
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:22,480
Really?

272
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:24,800
Yes. Also, look.

273
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:26,120
Over here.

274
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,040
Su Zaizai,

275
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:28,080
Jiang Jia,

276
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:29,840
have you turned in your math homework yet?

277
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:32,040
Are you guys

278
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,680
copying homework?

279
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,240
You're right!

280
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,960
We just have one question left.

281
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:43,960
{\an8}We're done. Here you go.

282
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:59,000
Wang Nan's footsteps don't make a sound.

283
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:01,560
Luckily, he didn't see it.

284
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:03,560
It's okay. You didn't write your name.

285
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,000
That's true.

286
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:08,360
Zaizai, is the letter with you?

287
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,880
I think I stuck it in my homework.

288
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:13,440
Where is my homework?

289
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,120
I just turned it in.

290
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,360
There are so many people.

291
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:42,120
We're done for.

292
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,080
It's okay.

293
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,720
Mr. Lin is a serious procrastinator.

294
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,520
He probably won't
grade our homework so soon.

295
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,120
Let's come back at lunch break.

296
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,200
All right.

297
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,000
Zhang Lurang,

298
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:01,640
I heard that Class 9's math papers
were mixed up with ours.

299
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,200
Ms. Zhang sent me to help you sort them.

300
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:04,520
It's fine. I'm almost done.

301
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,240
It's okay. Let me help you.

302
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,640
Su Zaizai got so many questions wrong.

303
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,560
She got almost all the main questions
at the back wrong.

304
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,680
If it were you,

305
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:20,520
I don't think you would want random people
looking through your papers.

306
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,319
I was just stating facts.

307
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:24,839
She was never good at math.

308
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,440
She wasn't even in our grade's top 100

309
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:27,760
in the last midterm exam.

310
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:28,960
Excluding science scores,

311
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:31,000
she would be in our school's top 20.

312
00:17:31,080 --> 00:17:32,640
Even including those scores,

313
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:33,760
I can be in the top 20.

314
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,800
Why can't I talk about her bad results?

315
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:40,800
MATH BOOK, SU ZAIZAI

316
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:43,480
She makes so many mistakes
even in her regular homework.

317
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,280
What is this?

318
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:50,120
"The first time I saw you,

319
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:52,120
you were sitting on the grass
and playing the guitar.

320
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,960
There were so many people around,

321
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:55,920
but I saw you right away."

322
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:59,080
Su Zaizai is writing a love letter
to someone.

323
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:00,880
Do you know this guitar player?

324
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:01,880
This is her privacy.

325
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:06,760
You only said that

326
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:08,120
because it belongs to Su Zaizai.

327
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:12,000
You can leave if you don't want to help.

328
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:20,720
MATH BOOK, SU ZAIZAI

329
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:28,800
Rangrang.

330
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:32,560
MATH BOOK, SU ZAIZAI

331
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:33,560
You're here as well.

332
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:45,680
The first one over here.

333
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:51,760
Rangrang,

334
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:55,960
did you see something?

335
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:01,640
No.

336
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,800
Your name is written so big

337
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,840
that it's unforgettable.

338
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:28,360
They're planning

339
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,960
to switch to a new student club

340
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:31,240
even before Qianyu leaves.

341
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:32,160
What do you mean?

342
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:35,640
Isn't that guy from the Guitar Club?

343
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:36,800
Is that so?

344
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:40,440
Su Zaizai is writing a love letter
to someone.

345
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:42,200
Do you know this guitar player?

346
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:47,720
Thank you.

347
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:48,800
You're welcome.

348
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:51,440
You can ask me directly
if you have questions about guitars.

349
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,560
{\an8}It's a good thing we asked him.

350
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:58,400
Otherwise, it would be so embarrassing

351
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,080
if Qianyu saw the absurd music theories

352
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,080
that I wrote in the letter.

353
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:05,040
Zhang Lurang!

354
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,880
Are Guan Fang and I invisible?

355
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:11,640
You've gained some self-awareness.

356
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:14,360
What were you two talking about over here?

357
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:15,800
You looked so excited.

358
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:18,240
It's a secret.

359
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:26,400
By the way,
we'll have a fitness test in this class.

360
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,200
The boys will be doing pull-ups.

361
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:30,000
How many can you do, Rangrang?

362
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:30,960
It's a secret.

363
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:39,760
Are you two the only ones left?

364
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:43,840
It's your turn. I'll hold your ankles.

365
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:45,800
Get ready.

366
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:49,360
Sir,

367
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:51,120
Mr. Xu sent me to ask you for the key

368
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,760
to the basketball equipment room.

369
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:54,240
Has Class 1 finished the fitness test?

370
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:57,080
The key.

371
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:58,920
I think I left it in the office.

372
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:01,600
I'll go and get it.

373
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:02,560
Sure.

374
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:04,760
You can record your own scores.

375
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:05,680
Okay.

376
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:12,960
I think you're more reliable.

377
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:14,560
You don't seem likely to cheat.

378
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:15,880
Record their scores for me.

379
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,040
Okay.

380
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,600
Ready.

381
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:26,640
Start.

382
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:53,440
Thirty seconds left.

383
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:57,440
Twenty-two.

384
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,960
Twenty-one.

385
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:02,120
It's 22.

386
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,880
Non-standard sit-ups don't count.

387
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:26,680
Time is up.

388
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,880
You guys did 36, right?

389
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:31,840
Thirty.

390
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:34,080
You did 26.

391
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:36,000
You just passed the test.

392
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:38,800
Rangrang,

393
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:41,440
you're truly stern and impartial.

394
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:57,520
Rangrang, are you having a bad day?

395
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:04,520
No.

396
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:06,960
Are you still denying it?

397
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:08,360
You touched your neck.

398
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,560
Rangrang,

399
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:17,760
did you see something?

400
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,360
No.

401
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:23,440
Your name is written so big

402
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:26,040
that it's unforgettable.

403
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:28,960
You didn't see

404
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:30,160
what I put

405
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:31,440
in my homework, did you?

406
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:36,400
Could it be that you thought

407
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,680
I wrote that for someone else

408
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:40,120
and got jealous?

409
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,120
No.

410
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:47,000
I have to lecture you about this.

411
00:23:47,080 --> 00:23:48,760
You couldn't even recognize my handwriting

412
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:50,960
after all the tutoring classes we've had.

413
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,560
This is so heartbreaking.

414
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:55,680
As a punishment,

415
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:59,200
you should read my notes carefully again.

416
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:00,760
You'll have to remember it this time.

417
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:05,360
As for making me suffer in PE class,

418
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:06,560
I'll forgive you.

419
00:24:19,120 --> 00:24:20,040
Lurang,

420
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:22,520
I warmed up some milk
and made some for you too.

421
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:24,080
Thank you, Uncle.

422
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,800
What happened to make you so happy?

423
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:35,840
I...

424
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:42,680
SU ZAIZAI'S EXCLUSIVE SECRET

425
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:46,280
All right. Go to bed early.

426
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:47,840
Remember to drink the milk.

427
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:48,800
Okay.

428
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:05,640
Qianyu?

429
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:06,920
What brings you to the Grade 10 area?

430
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:09,120
I need to go
to the Office of Academic Affairs.

431
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:12,960
Are you leaving very soon?

432
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:15,600
I'm leaving in about two weeks.

433
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,760
Two weeks. That's so soon.

434
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:22,800
I have one more recital
before I go abroad.

435
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:24,120
If you have time,

436
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,280
you can come and watch it.

437
00:25:25,840 --> 00:25:26,800
Consider it a farewell.

438
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:30,560
ADMISSION TICKET

439
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:49,000
ADMISSION TICKET

440
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,960
Qianyu only gave me this ticket.

441
00:25:54,560 --> 00:25:55,880
Does this mean

442
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:58,280
that I'm special?

443
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:02,040
ADMISSION TICKET

444
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:10,000
Two days ago, you were so upset

445
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:11,520
about Qianyu leaving the country.

446
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:13,400
Why are you in such a good mood today?

447
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,120
You're over the moon.

448
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,240
Did you win the lottery?

449
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:21,640
You can say that.

450
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:23,160
It's a good thing anyway.

451
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:26,840
Why do you all
have good things going on recently?

452
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:29,080
Lurang is also in a good mood today
for some reason.

453
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,600
So what's up? You haven't told us yet.

454
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:37,960
Don't envy me

455
00:26:38,040 --> 00:26:39,240
after I tell you guys about it.

456
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,880
Qianyu invited me to his recital

457
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:44,400
next Friday night.

458
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,920
So?

459
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:50,320
So

460
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,360
I won't be joining you guys that day.

461
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,800
I'm letting you know in advance.

462
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:55,600
Why won't you be joining us?

463
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:56,960
We're going as well.

464
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,240
Qianyu was at the basketball court

465
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:00,240
during lunch.

466
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:01,480
He told us about it.

467
00:27:01,560 --> 00:27:02,680
He even invited all of us.

468
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:06,240
So I wasn't the only one.

469
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:09,760
What's wrong with her now?

470
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:13,520
Her special prize became a pity award.

471
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:55,360
Why do you have tutoring

472
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:56,960
with Zhang Lurang on the weekend?

473
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:58,560
<i>The monthly exam is coming up.</i>

474
00:27:58,640 --> 00:28:00,120
<i>You know how poorly I scored</i>

475
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,240
<i>on the last math exam.</i>

476
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:04,280
Who will go shoe shopping with me then?

477
00:28:04,360 --> 00:28:06,040
He Yu and Fu Yao are both busy.

478
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:08,240
<i>Why don't you ask Guan Fang?</i>

479
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:10,680
<i>A guy might provide a different insight.</i>

480
00:28:13,120 --> 00:28:14,200
You have a point.

481
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:16,120
Then I'll ask him.

482
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:22,800
Hello, Guan Fang? Are you free tomorrow?

483
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:25,520
Grocery shopping with your grandma?

484
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:28,640
Never mind then. Bye.

485
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:36,880
Who else can I ask?

486
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:45,800
Do you have any other plans?

487
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:47,000
You're all dressed up

488
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:48,760
as if you're meeting someone important.

489
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:50,880
What? That's nonsense!

490
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:52,360
Don't put it like that.

491
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:53,800
This is how I usually dress.

492
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:55,520
Don't flatter yourself.

493
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:58,760
I didn't say it was me.

494
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:01,120
Let's get going. It's getting late.

495
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:02,800
How could you not

496
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:05,200
show appreciation
for what you've been given?

497
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:06,520
I freed up my busy schedule

498
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:07,760
to go shopping with you,

499
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,200
but you don't have any gratitude.

500
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,600
But then again,

501
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:14,840
am I the only one here today?

502
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,480
Yes, it's just you.

503
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:19,600
You have a good taste

504
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:21,280
for choosing me.

505
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:23,480
This had nothing to do with my taste.

506
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:24,720
I asked everyone else.

507
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:25,800
You're the only one free.

508
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:27,720
-I...
-Wait, no.

509
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:29,360
My elderly neighbor was free as well,

510
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:31,600
but I was worried
his fashion sense would be outdated.

511
00:29:31,680 --> 00:29:33,360
So on second thought, I went with you.

512
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:35,560
At least you're a boy.

513
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:37,520
Your tastes should differ
from that of a girl.

514
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,720
What did you mean by "at least"?

515
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:50,600
How pretty.

516
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,000
Try them on if you find them pretty.

517
00:30:01,080 --> 00:30:02,000
Forget it.

518
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:03,400
I'm not here to buy these today.

519
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:13,560
Excuse me. I would like to try these on.

520
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:21,680
That was close.

521
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:23,720
You've clearly never worn heels before.

522
00:30:23,800 --> 00:30:24,920
Why did you still buy them?

523
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:26,880
I'm a size 37.

524
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,000
These are size 37 shoes.

525
00:30:28,080 --> 00:30:29,320
They should fit me.

526
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:30,480
Besides,

527
00:30:30,560 --> 00:30:31,680
I'm already walking

528
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:33,160
much more steadily, okay?

529
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:52,640
{\an8}But didn't you like
that pair of sneakers a lot?

530
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:56,840
We have to make choices

531
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:57,840
about a lot of things.

532
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,320
We can't have it all.

533
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:06,520
Are you doing this for Qianyu's recital?

534
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:08,560
Why are you asking the obvious?

535
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:12,440
If you were Qianyu,

536
00:31:12,520 --> 00:31:13,440
what would you think of me?

537
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:16,680
How would I know?

538
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:18,880
True.

539
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:20,080
You'll never be him.

540
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:25,720
Still, thank you

541
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:27,600
for shopping with me for so long today.

542
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:29,800
Nobody has been so patient
with me for a long time.

543
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:30,800
I'm very happy.

544
00:31:43,560 --> 00:31:44,480
Let me get that.

545
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:46,040
Thank you.

546
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:51,400
{\an8}<i>Traces of the youthful thoughts that year</i>

547
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:53,120
{\an8}<i>seemed to have been exposed</i>

548
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:54,520
{\an8}<i>along with the early summer.</i>

549
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:57,200
Sorry. Please excuse me.

550
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:00,440
<i>Then they put on a not-so-clever disguise.</i>

551
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:03,720
<i>He created a safe area with his arms,</i>

552
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:06,520
<i>but blamed the heat</i>

553
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:07,920
<i>for his sweaty palms.</i>

554
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:12,440
<i>And only one of the two parties knew</i>

555
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:14,960
<i>that the seemingly coincidental encounter</i>

556
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:16,080
<i>was actually a calculation</i>

557
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:17,960
<i>more sophisticated than a math problem.</i>

558
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:22,440
<i>The gifts
they mustered the courage to give</i>

559
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,960
<i>were cloaked in mischief.</i>

560
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,520
<i>They chose
to silently say in their hearts,</i>

561
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:30,680
<i>"I want you to be happy."</i>

562
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:37,280
<i>However, love would always
quietly slip out</i>

563
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:40,280
<i>in every glance at him</i>

564
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:42,320
<i>and secretly written</i>

565
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:43,800
<i>into a diary under a desk lamp.</i>

566
00:32:44,280 --> 00:32:47,440
<i>These trivial and scrupulous moments</i>

567
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:50,360
<i>are like the candy
a child hides in their pocket.</i>

568
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:53,480
<i>If we unwrap the candy
and sniff it during the night,</i>

569
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:55,560
<i>the next day would seem</i>

570
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:57,280
<i>a little more worth anticipating.</i>

571
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:03,000
<i>Let's all relax</i>

572
00:33:03,080 --> 00:33:04,640
<i>after such a long class.</i>

573
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:06,200
<i>Let's play a game of imitation.</i>

574
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:08,880
<i>We shall start with Guan Fang.</i>

575
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,080
<i>Each of you will imitate an animal.</i>

576
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:12,040
<i>Begin.</i>

577
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:46,240
<i>Hurry up.</i>

578
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,720
<i>Rangrang is cuter
than a kitty in every way.</i>

579
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:57,760
<i>No, to me,</i>

580
00:33:57,840 --> 00:34:00,160
<i>he is even cuter than cute.</i>
